Trails 1-5 are the most challenging ones and require good physical strength from anyone, who goes there. Paths 6-10 are more relaxing and family-oriented. Itâ€™s only 1,900 meters to get up, but even such a short distance gives you quite a strong muscle pain for the next couple of days. So get ready for it!

Xingshe is a great place for a family trip and anyone who would like to experience and learn something new!  And finally, you donâ€™t need to be a great hiker to visit this place haha :)

We barely have disputes about places to visit! However, it's always very hard for us to find restaurants where both of us can enjoy meals because we have totally different tastes! Like a majority of Russians, I can't tolerate spicy food at all, while Patrick is a huge fan of everything that is tongue burning. I prefer to eat familiar dishes, while Patrick always likes to try something new, even if it looks too special. I love eating soups (in Russia, we barely live a day without eating a bowl of chunky soup, sometimes it's our main meal), so I'm fond of HOT POT! While Patrick mostly prefers dry food and his all-time loved meal is BBQ! 

We decided to make a competition, and finally choose what's better, hot pot or BBQ. For that, each of us has picked a restaurant to impress one another. Let's see who will win!
